}{\plain \fs24 \f1 \tab }{\plain \fs24 \b\f1 1-3.}{\plain \fs24 \f1   The precise Virgilian text that lies behind Dante's generically 'Virgilian' opening \softline
flourish is debated.  Major candidates include }{\plain \fs24 \i\f1 Aen}{\plain \fs24 \f1 . III.147, }{\plain \fs24 \i\f1 Aen}{\plain \fs24 \f1 . IV.522-528, }{\plain \fs24 \i\f1 Aen}{\plain \fs24 \f1 . VIII.26-27 \softline
