}{\plain \fs24 \f1 \tab }{\plain \fs24 \b\f1 28.}{\plain \fs24 \f1   This flat statement that Paul's journey actually occurred contrasts with the less \softline
forthright claim made for Aeneas's in verse 12: 'Tu dici che' (You tell that).  This and the \softline
subsequent phrasing, in which that same journey is referred to as the 'andata onde li dai tu vanto' \softline
(journey for which you grant him glory) at v. 25, both imbue the speaker's acceptance of the \softline
