Press, 1989), pp. 26-29.  Those who argue for an allegorical reading of the three ladies in heaven \softline
(see note to }{\plain \fs24 \i\f1 Inf}{\plain \fs24 \f1 . II.102) might do well to contemplate the fact that the first allegorical readings \softline
were developed by those who thought the nameless state of the first of them pointed in that \softline
